de insight into the world of Mah Meri speakers. Two finder lists (English–Mah Meri and Malay–Mah Meri) are included, giving access to the intended audience of international and local scholars and community members. The volume also includes a general introduction to the Mah Meri, notes to assist the reader in using the dictionary, and a short grammatical description.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 0aEnglish languagevDictionariesxMah Meri. 0aMah Meri languagevDictionariesxEnglish. 0aMah Meri languagevDictionariesxMalay. 0aMalay languagevDictionariesxMah Meri. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Southeast Asian Languages (see also Vietnamese).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHawaii eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486056140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824860561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824860561.jpg  a978-3-11-056414-3  Hawaii eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles